{"word":"προσαυδάω","slug":"προσαυδάω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>προσαυδάω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ήσω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to speak to, address, accost</i>, <el>τινά</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Tragic, in Tragic Greek'>Trag.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to address</i> words <i>to</i> one, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to speak of</i>, <el>τύχαν σέθεν</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>ἀδελφὴ προσηυδώμην</el> <i>was addressed as</i> sister, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}